Subject: I2P Invisible Internet Project
Description: The Invisible Internet Project (I2P) is a computer network layer that allows applications to send messages to each other pseudonymously and securely. Uses include anonymous Web surfing, chatting, blogging and file transfers.  Speakers include:Pat Baker - Track: Tech  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: Projector

Subject: TOR: Layers of Anonymity
Description: Tor is free software for enabling anonymous communication.  Tor directs Internet traffic through a free, worldwide, volunteer network consisting of relays to conceal a user's location and usage. Let's peel back the layers.  Speakers include:Pat Baker - Track: Tech  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: Projector
